document_data.caption: A map showing a portion of Manycats Alley and surroundings in the North Ward of Waterdeep.
document_data.name: Manycats Alley
document_data.mainbody: '''Manycats Alley''' was a small back alley that was located in the city of [[Waterdeep]].{{Cite interactive atlas|Waterdeep}}
document_data.Location: Manycats Alley was located in the northern section of Waterdeep's [[Waterdeep/Castle Ward|Castle Ward]] and the western section of the [[Waterdeep/North Ward|North Ward]]. The alley ran east to west in between [[Copper Street]] and [[Sul Street]]. Manycats Alley was also intersected by [[Shield Street]].
document_data.Description: Manycats Alley was notable for the presence of a large number of roaming [[cat]]s, which gave the alley its name, and a wide assortment of carved stone heads that decorated the buildings lining the alley. The carved heads were so life-like that many locals believed them to be the petrified remains of once living people.
